      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Minced Garlic",
      "amount": "1 clove"
    },
    {
      "name": "Fresh Thyme Sprigs (for garnish)",
      "notes": "optional"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 350°F.",
    "Place the pork back ribs on a baking sheet lined with aluminum foil. Season them lightly with salt and pepper.",
    "Mix ketchup, sour relish, honey, and minced garlic in a small bowl. Pour this mixture over the ribs evenly.",
    "Bake for about 1 hour, or until the meat is tender and nicely caramelized on top. Keep an eye to prevent burning.",
    "Garnish with fresh thyme sprigs if desired before serving."
